text: Racquetball competitions at the 2019 Pan American Games in Lima, Peru was held between August 2 and 10, 2019 at the Racquetball courts located at the Villa Deportiva Regional del Callao cluster. Six medal events were contested, a singles, doubles and team events for both men and women. A total of 60 athletes qualified to compete at the games. ==Medal table== ==Medalists== ===Men's events=== {| |- |rowspan=2| Men's singles |rowspan=2| |rowspan=2| | |- | |- |rowspan=2| Men's doubles |rowspan=2| Javier Mar Rodrigo Montoya |rowspan=2| Conrrado Moscoso Roland Keller | Rocky Carson Charles Pratt |- | Andrés Acuña Felipe Camacho |- |rowspan=2|Men's team |rowspan=2| Carlos Keller Conrrado Moscoso Roland Keller |rowspan=2| Sebastian Franco Mario Mercado | Jake Bredenbeck Rocky Carson Charles Pratt |- | Álvaro Beltrán Javier Mar Rodrigo Montoya |} ===Women's events=== {| |- |rowspan=2| Women's singles |rowspan=2| |rowspan=2| | |- | |- |rowspan=2| Women's doubles |rowspan=2| Paola Longoria Samantha Salas |rowspan=2| Gabriela Martínez María Rodríguez | Kelani Lawrence Rhonda Rajsich |- | Natalia Méndez María José Vargas |- |rowspan=2|Women's team |rowspan=2| Paola Longoria Montserrat Mejía Samantha Salas |rowspan=2| Natalia Méndez María José Vargas | Kelani Lawrence Rhonda Rajsich |- | Angélica Barrios Valeria Centellas Jenny Daza |} ==Participating nations== A total of 14 countries qualified athletes. The number of athletes a nation entered is in parentheses beside the name of the country. * * * * * * * * * * * * * * ==Qualification== A total of 60 racquetball athletes qualified compete. Each nation may enter a maximum of 8 athletes (four per gender). In each gender there will be a total of 30 athletes qualified, with the 2019 Pan American Championships being used to determine the countries qualified. Peru as host nation did not qualify any athletes automatically. ==References== ==External links== *Results book Category:Events at the 2019 Pan American Games 2019 Category:2019 in racquetball
